org.openadaptor.auxil.expression
Class UnaryOperation

java.lang.Object
  org.openadaptor.auxil.expression.UnaryOperation
All Implemented Interfaces:
IPostfixFunction
public class UnaryOperation
extends java.lang.Object
implements IPostfixFunction

Implementation of several unary postfix function.

It expects one non-null operand Objects on the stack, and will present the result back on the stack.

  • Null operand, or operands which the implementing class cannot handle will result in MathExceptions.
  • The class of the result depends on the incoming operand type, and the implementing class

Author:
Eddy Higgins

execute

public void execute(java.util.Stack stack)
             throws ExpressionException
Execute a unary operation.

This will take the top operand on the stack and call operate() with it. The result will then be pushed back on the stack.

Specified by:
execute in interface IPostfixFunction
Parameters:
stack - Stack containing at least one item.
Throws:
ExpressionException - if the Stack doesn't have an item, or if operate() fails.

return unary minus of supplied argument.

If argument is a Double or Float, then a Double will be returned. Otherwise a Long will be returned. Argument must be a non-null Number instance or an ExpressionException will be thrown.
